Ta1@bB@!T!1@CSURVOMON@;SUR-SAVE0@&Tb0@üTgC1@C1@C!@C1@C1@SCRATCH €Bµü/MONITOR-RETURN (back to the current work)MONITOR is a sucro family for monitoring contents of various files(typically Survo data and matrix files) during the work.At first a text file MONITOR.TXT must be created. It lists thefiles to be monitored by giving a suitable show command for each ofthem.Example:SAVEP CUR+1,CUR+2,MONITOR.TXTMAT LOAD A.MATMAT LOAD B.MATMonitoring is started by the command/MONITOR-START(an empty line below the command) and it calls another Survo session,MonitorSurvo, by placing its main window to the right of the currentwindow.Thereafter MonitorSurvo will display the contents of the files usingthe commands given in MONITOR.TXT.The contents of MONITOR.TXT can be edited during the workthus enabling dynamic removal and insertion of files to be monitored.Monitoring is stopped by activating/MONITOR-EXITwhich terminates MonitorSurvo and closes its window.The flash demoµhttp://www.survo.fi/flash/e_monitor.htmlshows a typical application and tells more about the details.              *  *  *Some options:After creating MONITOR.TXT, the files to be monitored may be deletedby the command/MONITOR-DELETEThe default setting for the window of MonitorSurvo can be alteredby giving the /MONITOR-START command with a series of commandsselecting the place and the size of the new window, for example, as/MONITOR-STARTWINDOW 14,0,550  / font size 14, position (0,550)TgC1@C1@C!@C1@C1@Tÿ

